[h1]The font-style Property [/h1]

The font-style property is typically used to specify italic text.

[b]The HTML:[/b] [code format="html" ]<p class="italic">This is a paragraph in italic style.</p>[/code]
[b]The CSS:[/b] [code format="css" codeId="514"]p.italic {
   font-style: italic;
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2591" width="100%"]

[h1]The font-style Property [/h1]

The font-style property has three values: [b]normal[/b], [b]italic[/b], and [b]oblique[/b]. 
Oblique is very similar to italic, but less supported. 

[b]The HTML: [/b] [code format="html" ]<p class="normal">This paragraph is normal.</p>
<p class="italic">This paragraph is italic.</p>
<p class="oblique">This paragraph is oblique.</p>[/code]
[b]The CSS:[/b] [code format="css" codeId="515"]p.normal {
   font-style: [b]normal[/b];
}
p.italic {
   font-style: [b]italic[/b];
}
p.oblique {
   font-style: [b]oblique[/b];
}[/code]
[note]The HTML [b]<i> [/b]tag will produce exactly the same result as the [b]italic font style[/b]. [/note]
